HEADWORD: Datril
<hw>Datril</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an analgesic derived from
acetanolide; also used as an antipyretic; Datril and Tylenol are
trademarks of brands of acetaminophen tablets. See
<er>acetaminophen</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> acetaminophen, Tylenol.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

